urocentric environment from which it was born. Intervening in a resurgent sociology of intellectuals, Zygmunt Bauman and the West re-evaluates the place of the West in social and political thought.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivilization, Westerny20th century. 0aCivilization, Western. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aEurocentrism.  aEurope.  aHolocaust.  aIsrael.  aJudaism.  aPoland.  aSoviet Union.  aStalinism.  aUnited Kingdom.  acamps.  acolonialism.  acommunism.  aconcentration.  aculture.  adecolonization.  aentangled.  aessayism.  agenocide.  ahistories.  amodernity.  amultiplicity.  apolitics.  atheory.  awar.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228018193?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228018193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228018193/original  a978-3-11-127195-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-143542-8  ACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles